'''''Study South Africa''''' is an annual publication of the [[International Education Association of South Africa]] (IEASA) in association with [[Universities South Africa]] (USAf), and serves as a guide to [[higher education]] in [[South Africa]]<ref name='studysa'>{{cite journal |title=Credits |journal=Study South Africa |date=2018 |page=[3] |url=http://hdl.handle.net/10962/65321 |accessdate=21 November 2018}}</ref>. ''Study South Africa'' is also know as ''Study South Africa: the guide to South African Higher Education''.
== Scope == The monograph series includes articles pertaining to [[internationalization]] within the Higher Education environment of [[South Africa]]<ref name='studysa'></ref>. Each monogrph in the series is themed e.g. the 2018 issue was themed ''Advancing internationalisation in an era of transformation''
== Editors == *2001–2003: Andy Mason *2004-2004: Alexandra van Essche *2005–2008: Roshen Kishun *2009–2016: Nico Jooste *2017-curent: Orla Quinlan
